# Repo Conventions

## Structure
- `src/model_monitor/ingestion/` — data loading only
- `src/model_monitor/metrics/` — metric computation only
- `src/model_monitor/decision/` — model health logic only
- `src/model_monitor/reporting/` — output and reporting only
- `src/model_monitor/utils/` — shared helpers
- `notebooks/exploration/` — exploration only, never imported by src/
- `configs/thresholds.yaml` — all threshold values live here, never hardcoded

## Rules
- Keep the four layers strictly separate: ingestion → metrics → decision → reporting
- `decision/` must use deterministic logic only — no LLM calls, ever
- `ModelHealth` outcomes are exactly: `VALID`, `NEEDS_CALIBRATION`, `INVALID`
- Thresholds go in `configs/thresholds.yaml`, never hardcoded in Python
- Notebooks are exploration only — no production logic in notebooks
- Write a stub test for every new module added under `src/`
- Do not add abstractions, base classes, or frameworks without being explicitly asked
